headline: ‘Upside Ahead’: Wells Fargo Says These 2 Cruise Stocks Are Set to Sail North
summary: The global cruise industry presents an interesting picture. While it has yet to fully recover from the disruptions of COVID-19, passenger volumes and revenues have been climbing consistently in recent years. Grand View Research valued the market at $7.67 billion in 2022 and projects it will grow to $18.3 billion by 2030, reflecting an estimated 11.5% CAGR over the forecast period. headline: 2 Reasons to Like RCL (and 1 Not So Much)
summary: Royal Caribbean has been treading water for the past six months, recording a small return of 3.4% while holding steady at $257.76. The stock also fell short of the S&P 500’s 11.3% gain during that period.
